On 3/2/07, Kenny MacLeod &lt;kennym@...&gt; wrote:
&gt;
&gt; org.junit.internal.requests.ClassRequest contains logic which selects
&gt; the appropriate Runner for use with a given test class.  This logic
&gt; includes picking the OldTestClassRunner for junit3 tests.
&gt;
&gt; This is great, since I have a large number of legacy junit3 tests
&gt; mixed in with some junit4 tests, and I can just pass them all to
&gt; JunitCore and they work.
&gt;
&gt; However, in a few cases, I have junit 3 tests with a static suite()
&gt; method.  Junit4 can handle this using the AllTests runner, but
&gt; unfortunately the code in ClassRequest ddoes not make use of AllTests
&gt; which decided which runner to use.
&gt;
&gt; Could ClassRequest be altered to detect if AllTests should be used,
&gt; rather just handing the test straight to OldTestClassRunner?
